<refsynopsisdiv id="bgmaster_server_refresh_config.synopsis">
    <title>Synopsis</title>
    <cmdsynopsis><command>
bgmaster_server_refresh_config [ OPTIONS ] filename
</command>
    </cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1 id="bgmaster_server_refresh_config.options">
    <title>Arguments</title>
    <para>Accepted arguments:</para>
    <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
            <term><option>--help</option></term>
            <listitem>
            <para>usage </para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term><option>filename</option></term>
            <listitem>
            <para>bg.properties configuration file to use </para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term><option>--host host:port</option></term>
            <listitem>
            <para>TCP host and port pair to use to connect to bgmaster_server </para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term><option>--verbose verbosity</option></term>
            <listitem>
            <para>Add program trace information.  Levels of verbosity are TRACE, DEBUG, INFO, WARN, ERROR, FATAL. </para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

    </variablelist>

</refsect1>

<refsect1 id="bgmaster_server_refresh_config.description">
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>Update bgmaster_server's configuration with a new or changed properties file.  If no properties file is given, it uses the default.  Note that updates to bgmaster policies are additive only.  Existing policy parameters may not be changed, deleted or replaced, but new ones may be added.</para>
</refsect1>


